1. Executive Summary 
ReelMind solves a problem that every heavy Instagram user eventually hits: saved reels  become a second doom-scroll. A user saves hundreds of reels across skincare, fitness,  haircare, and nutrition — and when they actually need a specific recommendation, finding it  requires scrolling through an unorganised wall of content. The save folder becomes as noisy as  the feed itself. 
ReelMind is a mobile application that intercepts shared reel URLs via the native iOS/Android  share sheet, automatically transcribes and categorises the content using AI, and stores it in a  personal, queryable knowledge base. Users can then ask natural-language questions — 'what  sunscreen for oily skin under ₹500 did I save?' — and receive a structured, conversational  answer backed by their own saved content and supplemented by web search. 
The core insight: at save time, the user has no immediate intent. That processing window is  used to do all the expensive AI work upfront, so that query time is near-instant. The experience  feels like a personal AI assistant who has watched every reel you've ever saved. 
2. Problem Statement 
2.1 The Pain Point
