ReelMind — Product Requirements Document | CONFIDENTIAL 
How it works 
• User taps Share on any public Instagram reel, selects ReelMind from the share sheet. • App receives the reel URL. If the URL is inaccessible (private account, region block,  deleted reel), the app notifies the user immediately with a specific error and does not  attempt processing. 
• Audio is extracted and transcribed using OpenAI Whisper. Caption text, hashtags, and  creator handle are also extracted. 
• All extracted text is sent to an LLM (Claude / GPT-4o) with a classification prompt. The  model returns a category and a confidence score. 
◦ Confidence ≥ 0.75: reel is auto-assigned to the category. 
◦ Confidence < 0.75: reel is placed in the Uncategorised inbox. 
• The full transcript is chunked, embedded via a text embedding model, and stored in the  vector database alongside metadata (reel URL, creator handle, category, thumbnail URL,  timestamp). 
• A push notification is sent: 'Saved to Skincare — tap to reassign.' User can reply inline  (WhatsApp-style) with a category name, and the reel is moved immediately. 
5.2 Library View 
Home screen layout 
• Home screen shows a horizontal scroll of category pills (Skincare, Haircare, Bodycare,  Fitness, Nutrition, Fashion, + user-created categories, + Uncategorised badge if count >  0). 
• Tapping a category shows a vertical scroll of saved reel cards: thumbnail, creator handle,  2-line auto-summary, date saved. 
• Long-press on a card reveals: Reassign Category, Delete, Open in Instagram. • Uncategorised inbox is always visible as a badge on the home screen so the user never  loses content. 
5.3 Chat Query — Per Category 
Query experience 
• Each category has a chat icon / 'Ask' button that opens a conversation scoped to that  category. 
• At query time: the user's question is embedded and matched against the vector DB  (filtered by category). The top-k most relevant reel chunks are retrieved. 
• If retrieved chunks provide sufficient context, the LLM generates a response using only  saved content. If context is thin (fewer than 2 relevant matches above similarity  threshold), web search is triggered automatically.
