• The response is rendered as a chat message followed by 2–4 rich cards. Each card  contains: reel thumbnail, creator handle, a 2-line extract from the transcript, and a 'Watch  Reel' deep-link button to Instagram. 
• Web-sourced content is clearly labelled 'From the web' with the source URL. • Conversation history within a session is maintained — follow-up questions work naturally. 
5.4 Global Search 
Cross-category queries 
• A search bar on the home screen allows queries across all categories simultaneously. • Technically identical to category query — same RAG pipeline, no category filter applied. • Response cards include a category badge so users know where each result came from. 
5.5 Notification Reply — Category Assignment 
WhatsApp-style inline reply 
• On save notification: 'Saved to Uncategorised — reply with a category name to assign.' • User replies with a text string (e.g. 'Makeup'). App creates the category if it doesn't exist  and moves the reel. 
• Confirmation notification sent: 'Added to Makeup.' 
• iOS limitation note: notification reply character limit is 140 characters. If category name is  ambiguous (matches multiple existing categories partially), the app defaults to creating a  new one and the user can merge later. 
5.6 Edge Cases & Error Handling 
Known edge cases 
• Private reel URL: Detected at ingestion. Error notification sent. Reel is not stored. If a  previously public account goes private after a reel was saved, the stored transcript and  metadata are retained (we already have it). The 'Watch Reel' link will surface an  Instagram error — the card should degrade gracefully and show 'Content may be  unavailable.' 
• Deleted reel: Same graceful degradation. Transcript is retained for query purposes. • No audio / music-only reel: If Whisper returns an empty transcript, the system falls back to  caption + hashtag analysis only. If both are empty, the reel goes to Uncategorised. • Duplicate save: If the same reel URL is shared again, the app detects the duplicate,  notifies the user ('You already saved this on [date]'), and does not re-process. • Transcription failure: Reel is queued for retry (up to 3 attempts). On final failure, reel is  placed in Uncategorised with a flag indicating processing failed.
