6.2 Processing Architecture 
All expensive processing (transcription, embedding, classification) happens at save time via a  background job queue. This is the key architectural decision that makes query responses fast. 
• Save time: URL received → queued as a BullMQ job → Whisper transcription → LLM  classification → embedding → Supabase vector store → push notification. Expected total  time: 15–45 seconds depending on reel length. User is not waiting for this.
