• Query time: Question embedded → vector similarity search (Supabase pgvector) → top-k  chunks retrieved → LLM synthesis call → response streamed to client. Expected latency:  2–4 seconds. 
• Web search is triggered conditionally: if the number of retrieved chunks above the  similarity threshold is fewer than 2, Tavily search is called and its results are appended to  the LLM context. 
7. MVP Scope & Phasing 
Phase 1 — MVP (Months 1–3) 
• Share sheet ingestion for Instagram public reels. 
• Auto-categorisation into 6 preset lifestyle categories. 
• Uncategorised inbox with notification reply for category assignment. 
• Per-category chat query with rich card responses. 
• Global search bar (same RAG pipeline, no category filter). 
• Manual reassign and delete from library view. 
• User-created custom categories. 
• Graceful degradation for inaccessible / deleted / audio-less reels. 
Phase 2 — Post-MVP (Months 4–6) 
• Multi-platform support: TikTok, YouTube Shorts. 
• Product price comparison via Nykaa / Flas.io API integrations. 
• Cross-reel synthesis: 'What do all my saved creators say about retinol?' type  summarisation queries. 
• Private account support (if Instagram policy allows). 
• Android home screen widget for quick save. 
Phase 3 — Growth 
• Collaborative libraries (share a category with a friend). 
• Creator analytics: which creators appear most in your library. 
• Trend alerts: 'Three new reels about SPF 50 sunscreen this week based on your  interests.' 
